/*
:name: struct_init_whole_read
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: struct_init_whole_read.top
:pyrope_top: struct_init_whole_read.top
*/

// Regression for the slang net-initializer store drop (the CtrlBlock
// `_GEN_3923` "incompletely driven" category from the XiangShan Backend
// sweep). The golden .v declares a NESTED-struct wire whose initializer is a
// '{...} pattern reading fields of a const-indexed array-of-struct element,
// and the wire is then consumed only WHOLE (inside a concat) — never by
// field. The old emission gate split the initializer into per-field leaf
// stores only for all-scalar or read-by-field structs, so this shape stored
// to the FLAT name while every read resolved through the (never-written)
// bundle leaves: the emitted Pyrope declared the wire `= nil` with no store
// and failed "incompletely driven". A scalar-struct-var's reads always route
// through its leaves, so the initializer must split whenever the var is
// bundle-declared. Semantically the module forwards element 1's fields:
// out = {foldpc, ev, instr} of cfVec[1].
pub mod top(clock:u1, reset:u1,
            io_cfVec_0_valid:u1, io_cfVec_0_bits:u14,
            io_cfVec_1_valid:u1, io_cfVec_1_bits:u14) -> (io_out:u14@[]) {
  io_out = io_cfVec_1_bits
}
